[3] New Hampshire (Carroll County)
Date: Tue 24 Sep 2013
Source: Seattle pi, Associated Press (AP) report [edited]
http://www.seattlepi.com/news/science/article/Horse-with-EEE-found-in-Ossipee-NH-4839389.php


Public health officials say a horse from Ossipee [Carroll County] New Hampshire, has tested positive for eastern equine encephalitis.

A horse in Derry [Rockingham County] tested positive for the mosquito-borne disease last week [week of 16 Sep 2013]. The most recent finding, announced Tuesday [24 Sep 2013], raises the risk level for the town of Ossipee from "remote" to "high." The surrounding towns of Tamworth, Madison, Freedom, Effingham, Wakefield, Brookfield, Wolfeboro, Tuftonborough, and Moultonborough [Carroll County] will increase to a "moderate" risk level.

So far this season [2013], 13 mosquito batches have tested positive for West Nile virus and 20 have tested positive for EEE. One person in Chesterfield [Cheshire County] also has been diagnosed with West Nile virus.

Public health director Dr Jose Montero says people should protect against mosquito bites no matter where they live until there is a killing frost statewide.

